==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|lang=grc|en}} {{term|πολύγλωττος||lang=grc|tr=poluglottos}}, from {{term|πολύς||tr=polus|lang=grc|many}} + {{term|γλῶττα||lang=grc|tr=glōtta|tongue", "language}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pɒliːglɒt/}}

===Adjective===
'''polyglot'''

# Containing, or made up, of, several languages.
#: ''a '''polyglot''' lexicon; a '''polyglot''' Bible''
# Versed in, or speaking, many languages.

